parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering/brake fluid booster can cause the brakes and steering to lock up, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brakes and steering lock up while driving
especially around turns
making it difficult or impossible to control the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering linkage can cause the loss of steering ability, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering linkage is loose or about to fall out
causing the loss of steering ability.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Line Failure due to Corrosion
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of brake lines due to corrosion can cause a sudden loss of braking ability, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Brake pedal becomes soft or spongy
brake pedal travels to the floor
loss of braking ability
brake failure
rusting or corrosion of brake lines
bulging of brake lines.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Failure due to Rusted Brake Lines
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of brake lines due to rusting can cause a sudden loss of braking ability, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Brake pedal becomes soft or spongy
brake pedal travels to the floor
loss of braking ability
brake failure
rusting or corrosion of brake lines
bulging of brake lines.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of power while driving can cause accidents, especially when the vehicle is traveling at high speeds. This issue can also lead to difficulties in passing emissions tests and may result in liability concerns for the vehicle owner.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
gauges quit working
the check engine light comes on
and the vehicle may need to be restarted.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inaccurate speedometer readings can lead to unsafe driving conditions, as the driver may not be aware of their actual speed. This can cause accidents, especially when the speedometer displays incorrect speeds, such as 120mph when the vehicle is stationary.
symptoms: The speedometer displays inaccurate and erratic readings
sometimes showing speeds that are 20mph off
jumping to different speeds
or not moving at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The flickering of headlights can reduce visibility, especially at night or in low-light conditions, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The headlights flicker when the Stabilitrak system is engaged
related to steering wheel position and/or car attitude (bumps
etc.).

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and reduced power can cause the vehicle to lose speed and control, increasing the risk of accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls without warning
the engine power reduces
the vehicle cannot maintain speed
multiple lights on the dashboard remain on
including the engine light.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inaccurate speedometer readings can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or near-miss incidents.
symptoms: The speedometer shows inaccurate speeds
the speedometer does not register speed at all
the speedometer needle does not return to zero.
